  "prompt": "Who is the old man in the MDH Masala ads and why does he appear in all their ads?",
  "response": "The old man in the MDH Masala ads is Mahashay Dharampal Gulati, the founder of MDH (Mahashian Di Hatti), a well-known spice brand in India. He became the face of the brand and appeared in almost all of their advertisements, which contributed significantly to their popularity. \n\nHis presence in the ads helped establish a strong brand identity, as the audience associated him with quality and trust in spices. Mr. Gulati's warm persona and memorable catchphrase, \"Asli masala, asli swad\u201d (Real spices, real taste), made the commercials appealing and relatable to consumers. His role as a brand ambassador persisted even after his passing in 2020, as the company continued to honor his legacy and connection with the brand.",
